# Help: Additional virtio device drivers
#
# Virtio device classes beyond the mandatory virtio-blk,
# virtio-console, virtio-net, virtio-fs, and vsock. Adds:
# - VIRTIO_BALLOON: memory ballooning for host-driven guest reclaim
# - VIRTIO_INPUT: input devices (virtio-keyboard, virtio-mouse)
# - VIRTIO_MEM: hotpluggable guest memory (virtio-mem)
# - VIRTIO_PMEM: persistent memory exposed via virtio
# - VIRTIO_MMIO: MMIO-transport virtio (microvm machine, ARM virt)
#
# Prerequisites inlined per the self-containment rule:
# - MEMORY_HOTPLUG=y gates VIRTIO_MEM.
# - MEMORY_HOTREMOVE=y + MIGRATION=y also gate VIRTIO_MEM. These
#   are the full chain VIRTIO_MEM declares "depends on".
#
# Every symbol is tristate. No builtin/ counterpart is shipped
# because these modules are only needed when the matching
# device is attached.
# See: drivers/virtio/Kconfig
# See: drivers/misc/Kconfig (VIRTIO_BALLOON)
# See: drivers/nvdimm/Kconfig (VIRTIO_PMEM)

CONFIG_MEMORY_HOTPLUG=y
CONFIG_MEMORY_HOTREMOVE=y
CONFIG_MIGRATION=y
CONFIG_VIRTIO_BALLOON=m
CONFIG_VIRTIO_INPUT=m
CONFIG_VIRTIO_MEM=m
CONFIG_VIRTIO_PMEM=m
CONFIG_VIRTIO_MMIO=m
